</noscript></center><div class='main'><div class='mainheader'><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="178dc98989d669ff4092283ae3e60f13" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magic/articles/articles.php'>Video Games and Movies</option><option value='/wars/articles/articles.php'>Wizards Minis</option></select></td></form></tr></table></div><div class='maincontent'><font class="h1font"> Indy Clix Team Abilities and more<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/heroclix/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/heroclix/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/heroclix/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/heroclix/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/heroclix/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/heroclix/main/mpage.php?member=2570'>Cat "Ulaire Kubaz" Ceder</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/heroclix/main/mpage.php?member=2570&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> October 2, 2003</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> Greetings and welcome to another article.<br />
<br />
So it’s finally happened, Wizkids released Indy Clix . . . the long awaited, since it was announced clix of a lot of our favorite Independent characters, this article will show a few of the figures, and their benefits from their specific factions so sit back, grab a drink, ease back in your chair and enjoy.<br />
<br />
We’ll start with the factions for Indy Clix, if you haven’t read the website for Wizkids, its http://www.wizkidsgames.com so go there and check it out, or you can go to http://www.hcrealms.com for more info along with other interesting things.<br />
<br />
First off, 2000 A.D. their team ability allows you at any time during the game; you may declare an opposing team or characters as your target. Once the character or team is chosen, it may not be changed. All 2000 AD team members increase their attack value by 1 when attacking the chosen team or character.<br />
<br />
First off this is ability is probably one of the best that I’ve seen them come out with allowing all of  your 2000 AD characters add +1 to their attack, that’s a permanent perplex for their attack. Some of the more respectable characters that come with this particular team ability are the Judges. With that we have Brit City Judge, Johnny Alpha, Judge Anderson, Judge Alpha, Judge Death, Judge Dredd, Judge Fear, Judge Fire, Judge Hershey and Judge Mortis.<br />
<br />
Now if you’ve been to http://www.hcrealms.com or have purchased any Indy Clix already you’ll see that the Judges in any form are a nasty bunch. I’ve looked at all their stats and powers and I would personally be happy to have any of them on my team, especially Judge Death, he’s got some interesting play and I can see him being quite fun to play with.<br />
<br />
This is why I think he’ll be fun: <br />
<br />
U Judge Death, 141pts<br />
Speed: 8(st), 7, 6, 6, 6(ph), 6(ph), 8(st), 7, 6, 6, 0 KO<br />
Attack: 10, 9, 9, 8 (all b/c/f), 0, 0, 10, 9, 9, 8(all b/c/f) 0 KO<br />
Defense: 15(i), 14(i), 14(t), 13(t), 10(ip), 10(ip), 15(i), 14(i), 14(t), 13(t), 10(r) KO<br />
Damage: 3, 3, 3, 3, 0, 0, 3, 3, 3, 3, 0 (all bf) KO<br />
(st = Stealth, ph = phasing, b/c/f = Blades/Claws/Fangs, i = Invulnerability, t = toughness, ip = Imperviousness, bf = Battle Fury)<br />
<br />
The rest of the figures that compose 2000 AD are Nemesis, Stix Torquemada and Wulf Sternhammer, after taking a quick peak at them, I am pleased to say that almost any 2000 AD character is worth his weight, if nothing else for his Team Ability, but characters that fall under 2000 AD are quite beefy.<br />
<br />
The next group is CrossGen, when this character takes damage from an attack; it deals 1 damage to the attacker. This damage may not be evaded or reduced.<br />
Can you say Mystics . . . I’m glad to see that they actually made some CrossGen figures in this set instead of doing what they normally do and make the symbol for the team ability but not make anyone with the team ability. With this team ability we get the following figures. Bron, Yukio and the all powerful Samandahl Rey, which if you haven’t seen this man-beast you should check the stats on him . . .or just keep reading and I will show you them<br />
<br />
Samandahl Rey<br />
<br />
10(fb), 9 (fb), 8(fb), 7, 6, 8(pl), 8(pl), 6, 4<br />
11(ss), 10(ss), 9(ss), 8(ss), 7(tk), 8(tk), 8(tk), 6(ic), 5(ic)<br />
15(i), 15(i), 14(t), 14(t), 13(t), 13(i), 12(ip), 12(b), 12(b)<br />
3(o), 3(o), 3, 2, 2, 4(o), 4(o), 2(s), 2(s)<br />
<br />
Okay from CrossGen, another good Team Ability especially if you pack a lot of Wildcard Team Ability people you can make great use of their ability.<br />
<br />
Our next step for Team Abilities is Crusade; this one in my own opinion doesn’t make that much sense for an ability. All attack rolls made by members of the Crusade team that result in doubles (except two 1s) because knock back equal to the attacking character’s damage value.<br />
<br />
This would be a better ability if it didn’t already do what doubles does when you roll them, the only difference is however if you do double 2’s and your damage is 1 you knock them back 1 square, where as if they have Toughness, Invulnerability or Imperviousness, they still get knocked back. So again if you roll something like double 4’s and do 3damage and they have Toughness you still knock them back for 3 spaces instead of 2.<br />
<br />
Personally, I think they could’ve done something more with this ability, something with like a Charge-like ability since Crusades, combat on horses, etc . . . maybe it’s just me but any who, the people who have this ability are: Arashi, Death Demon, Shi and Tomoe . . . I personally like the Shi figure, great sculpt and well worth her points, again to check out these figures check either of the previous two websites that I gave you earlier.<br />
<br />
Okay our next Team Ability is Danger Girl, when a member of the Danger Girl team is chosen as the target of an attack, roll one six-sided die. On a result of a 6, the attack cannot be made; the character has fooled the attacker with a disguise or stunned them with good looks. The attacker must choose another target or take a different action with that character instead.<br />
<br />
I like this ability, I’ve always liked it, except when I am playing against it and it works for them instead of against them. Ah well, it’s still a great ability and some of the people that have the Danger Girl Team Ability are Abbey Chase, Natalia Kassle and Sydney Savage.<br />
<br />
Danger Girl, as a name, is probably one of the most common names in the Independent Universe and by far has one of the best figures in the game as well; I personally like V Abbey Chase which I will show right now<br />
<br />
Abbey Chase 52pts 8” range<br />
<br />
10(s), 9s), 8, 7, 6(s), 5(s)<br />
8(ee), 7(ee), 7(ee), 6, 6, 5<br />
14(ss), 14(ss), 14(ss), 13(ss), 13, 12<br />
2(o), 2(o), 2, 1, 1, 1<br />
(s = Stealth, ee = Energy Explosion, ss = Super Sense, o = Outwit)<br />
<br />
for her points she may not look like much, but she has the vaunted Outwit with Stealth like R Black Panther which I personally like, as well if she has Energy Explosion to do some damage from afar to the people that do base her and if she does get based, she has her Super Sense to fall back on in case she does get hit.<br />
<br />
So Danger Girl is definitely a dangerous girl and with that we move on to the next team ability and by far one of the best in the game, the Wildcard team ability<br />
<br />
BPRD (Bureau of Paranormal Research and Defense) Members of the B.P.E.D. team act as a wild cards. They can use any team ability that any friendly character on the battle map possess. They may use this ability once each action.<br />
<br />
YEAH! Wildcards, you know how much I love them since I’ve written an article about it and I vaunt about the Doombots, if you lived here you’d know what that meant, well with B.P.R.D. we have the biggest badin the game and some others to follow him. With that we have: Hellboy, Lobster Johnson and Rasputin, by far though, I have to give mad props to the sculpts for these figures and with that I’ll show you my favorite as I like to do . . . here’s U Hellboy<br />
<br />
Hellboy 188pts<br />
<br />
10(c), 8 (c), 8(c), 7, 7, 7, 6, 6, 6, 5, 5<br />
12(ss), 11(ss), 10(ss), 9(ss), 8(ss), 11, 12, 10, 9, 8, 7<br />
16(i), 16(i), 15(i), 15(t), 14(t), 14(i), 14(ip), 13(ip), 13(i), 12(t), 12(t)<br />
2(cc), 2(cc), 2(cc), 2(cc), 2(cc), 4(bf), 5(bf), 4(bf), 3(bf), 3, 2<br />
(c = charge, ss = Super Strength, i = Invulnerability, t = toughness, ip = Imperviousness, cc = Close Combat Expert, bf = Battle Fury)<br />
<br />
As you can se he’s a monster, and he’s probably one of the few people in the Independent Universe that can stand toe to toe with the Marvel Universe and the DC Universe. He’s got a shlew of different powers and he’s a very versatile piece, however, like Thanos, you’ll probably only see the Unique version in 400+ point games.<br />
<br />
Ah well, he’s still a monster, now we enter the realm of Kabuki, Any line of fire drawn to this character that passes through hindering terrain, including the square that this character occupies, is treated as through it has been drawn through blocking terrain.<br />
<br />
Ah, another fun ability, however Indy Clix doesn’t have someone that has the Superman Team ability so this one will make it a much more strategy based and more difficult to hit from range. However a lot of the Kabuki characters have Blades/Claws/Fangs so them staying in stealth might or might not be a problem. Of course crossing over another piece of terrain while fighting someone else may prove useful.<br />
<br />
Some of our characters that are on the Kabuki Team are obviously, Kabuki and then there’s Scarab, Siamese and Tiger Lily. I’ve seen Siamese, haven’t had the chance to play with her yet, but from what I saw I like, especially the sculpt for her and of course you know what that means . . . <br />
<br />
Siamese 55pts<br />
<br />
7, 6, 6, 5, 5, 4 (all Flurry)<br />
10(i), 9(i), 8(i), 7, 6, 5<br />
16(ss), 15(ss), 14(ss), 14(ss), 13, 12<br />
2, 2, 1, 1, 1, 1<br />
(i = Incapacitate)<br />
(ss = Super Senses)<br />
<br />
she’s not long lived, but she has Super Senses to help her along the way, her good thing is that she has Incapacitate of which with Flurry in base to base is nice, in other words your first his can be an Incapacitate hit then you can follow it up with another 2 points of damage, that’s the nice thing about Flurry/Incapacitate is that she can get by their Invulnerability/Toughness/Imperviousness by making them take a click of damage for their second action token. If they don’t have a token then you can double Incapacitate them which is always nice too.<br />
<br />
Well with Kabuki out of the way that leaves us one more Team Ability for Indy Clix and that’s the free movement of Top Cow, You may give a Top Cow team member a move action that does not count toward you allotment of actions for the turn.<br />
<br />
Simply stated free moves for all . . . always nice, and our Top Cow team consists of some really good figures, well at least I like them and they are Angelus, Aphrodite IX, Cyblade, Ian Nottingham, Magdalena, The Darkness and Witchblade.<br />
<br />
Witchblade, probably the most famous out of the entire set because of her television show that was on for a while, granted wasn’t all that good, but still it was a pretty cool show and since I have her on the mind why not show what she can do<br />
<br />
U Witchblade 66pts<br />
<br />
10(ch), 8, 8, 7, 6, 5, 5<br />
10(bcf), 9(bcf), 9(bcf), 8(bcf), 7(bcf), 6(bcf) 6<br />
16(t), 15(t), 14(t), 14(t), 13, 12(r), 12(r)<br />
3, 3, 3, 2, 2, 2, 1<br />
(ch = Charge, bcf = Blades/Claws/Fangs, t = Toughness, r = Regenerate)<br />
<br />
Now as you can see, she’s a beast in her own right, she has a charge of 10, giving her the ability to move 5 squares, then with and attack of 10 which is high for a lot of people she can more than likely hit her opponent, then she falls back on either doing 3 clicks to get past that Invulnerability or Toughness, or chance the BCF for a possible 6. <br />
<br />
Personally with this entire set I am pleased to see that a lot of BCFer’s do 3 base damage, which as I said gets you past the Invulnerability and Toughness, then once they get down to a more reasonable defense then you can open up with the BCF.<br />
<br />
Okay so now that all the Affiliated teams are taken care of lets look at the final faction of Indy Clix and that’s the Non-Affiliated group and then consist of Arwyn, Ashleigh, Boon, Bron, Hecate, Major Maxim and Saurian Trooper, out of them all and I can happily say Arwyn is my favorite and of course I pulled her in my booster pack that I go and so with that I will show here.<br />
<br />
Arwyn 68pts<br />
<br />
10(rs), 8(rs), 8(rs), 6, 6, 5<br />
11(ee), 10(ee), 9(ee), 9(ee), 8(ee), 7(ee)<br />
16(wp), 15(wp), 15(wp), 14, 14, 13<br />
1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1 (all Ranged Combat Expert)<br />
(rs = Running Shot, ee = Energy Explosion, wp = Will Power)<br />
<br />
Arwyn, the running archer, the seeker of the parts of the bow  . . . and more, but I don’t know her whole story, the beauty of this figure is that you can Running Shot someone for 1 click of damage, then on your next turn push her without taking any damage and then Range Combat Expert them for 3 more, thus doing 4 clicks of potential damage.<br />
<br />
Well there you have it, a list of the Team Abilities and how they work and what you will see in the upcoming Indy Clix game play. I am personally very glad that they made this set and made the new rules, I like them, and I just hope that I can get more people to play the game because I don’t want to see it die like other games.<br />
<br />
So in closing these are the Team Abilities and their benefits and some of the ideas that I have for the Indy Clix  . . . if you made it this far without having to go to the bathroom, or wake up from a nap I commend you. If you made it this far doing that, then I still commend you for reading the whole article.<br />
<br />
Thanks,<br />
Cat<br />
<br />
